race.comment: FLOREY (7) has returned in career best form and has more to offer third-up after just missing last time. Gun hoop Toeroek sticks and she should just blend into the race perfectly from the middle draw. Top pick. CIELAO (3) is a mare in great touch, and the form around her is superb. Expect her to have a tougher time of it in front this time but gets in well with the claim and is sure to be right there at the business end again. Can't knock. RUBINI (9) returned with a great effort here behind Arcandam, who has since won again. Gets in low at the weights and is boasts a good record over this track and trip. Strong each-way hope. SECOND FIX (6) made good ground in the run home to finish a close sixth in a blanket finish. Is sure to have come on from that and will take some stopping if settles closer. CAPTAIN JOOLIAN (1) comes in fresh after a good win on the Parks track. This looks a bit tough for him but he can sneak into a placing.
